<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Reset Database - Ethiopian Vote System</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css">
  <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/reset_database.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reset-container">
      <div class="warning-icon">
        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i>
      </div>
      <h2 class="warning-title">Danger Zone: Database Reset</h2>

      <div class="warning-message">
        <strong>WARNING:</strong> This action will permanently delete ALL data from the system except the original super admin account. This cannot be undone.
      </div>

      <div class="reset-details">
        <strong>The following data will be permanently deleted:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>All registered voters and their information</li>
          <li>All votes cast in the system</li>
          <li>All political parties (except default parties)</li>
          <li>All admin users (except original super admin)</li>
          <li>All audit logs and activity logs</li>
          <li>All system settings and configurations</li>
        </ul>
        <strong>Data that will be restored:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>Default political parties</li>
          <li>System configuration defaults</li>
          <li>Original super admin account</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <form method="POST" action="/admin/reset-database">
        <div class="form-group">
          <label class="form-label" for="confirm_reset">
            Type "RESET_ALL_DATA" to confirm:
          </label>
          <input type="text" id="confirm_reset" name="confirm_reset" class="form-control"
                 placeholder="RESET_ALL_DATA" required>
          <small style="color: #6c757d; margin-top: 5px; display: block;">
            This confirmation code is required to prevent accidental resets.
          </small>
        </div>

        <button type="submit" class="btn-reset">
          <i class="fas fa-trash-alt"></i> Reset Entire Database
        </button>
      </form>

      <a href="/admin/login" class="btn-cancel">
        <i class="fas fa-times"></i> Cancel - Return to Admin Panel
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
